      "stem_html": "<p>The following reaction involves a hydrolysis followed by an intramolecular nucleophilic acyl substitution reaction. Write both steps, and show their mechanisms.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBc0lZIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--c0befacecf84908efd84a8b8d673adfb7bf47f5f/OChem_23_EC_027.jpg\" alt=\"The reaction shows acid hydrolysis of 2-(2, 2, 4-trimethyl-1,3-dioxan-4-yl)acetic acid giving products in which the sixth carbon of a 3-hydroxy-3-methyl cyclohexanone ring is replaced by oxygen and a propan-2-one.\">",
